18:47.835 --> 18:50.712
Nice Wonder Wheel! Stop!

18:51.923 --> 18:55.842
[JACK SCREAMlNG]

18:56.511 --> 18:58.178
Stop the Wonder Wheel!

18:58.387 --> 19:01.973
Help! Wonder Wheel!

19:02.975 --> 19:05.727
I'm the Wonder Wheel
champion of the world!

19:05.895 --> 19:08.897
Miracle Wonder Wheel!
The best one!

19:09.065 --> 19:10.065
[AIR HISSlNG]

19:10.233 --> 19:14.069
The best... Oh, Wonder Wheel, don't.
Wonder Wheel.

19:14.946 --> 19:17.239
Come on, Wonder Wheel.
Don't. You can't.

19:17.406 --> 19:19.407
We've been through
too much together.

19:19.575 --> 19:22.160
Come on! Come on, Wonder Wheel.

19:22.370 --> 19:24.329
Come on, you can do it,
Wonder Wheel.

19:24.497 --> 19:27.791
I don't wanna go through life
being a Wonder Wheel murderer.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.252
I want you to play with kids.

19:30.419 --> 19:33.088
You haven't even been to the zoo.

19:33.256 --> 19:35.632
You never even touched water.

19:35.842 --> 19:38.760
Come on, Wonder Wheel. Don't die.

19:38.928 --> 19:41.096
Wonder Wheel, don't die.

19:41.264 --> 19:43.390
Please, Wonder Wheel.

19:44.559 --> 19:47.769
Please, Wonder Wheel...

19:47.937 --> 19:49.938
[GRUNTlNG]

19:57.280 --> 19:59.656
I know what I want.
He likes Wonder Wheel.

19:59.866 --> 20:02.951
Let's blow it up right away.
The black man.

20:04.620 --> 20:07.038
He wants one in black, all right?

20:07.248 --> 20:11.293
The black man.
He wants the black man.

20:12.587 --> 20:16.673
No. No, Eric, no. Not today.
Not now. Not never.

20:17.466 --> 20:19.509
Yes.
He's not a toy.

20:19.719 --> 20:22.679
He's trouble. See the mustache?
I asked him to shave.

20:22.889 --> 20:24.806
Mr. Morehouse, l really don't care.

20:24.974 --> 20:27.183
But he's one of our cleaning people.

20:27.393 --> 20:29.352
I want him.
He's not for sale.

20:29.562 --> 20:32.480
Why not?
Because he's a person.

20:32.648 --> 20:36.026
Daddy said anything l wanted,
anything in the store.

20:36.235 --> 20:39.404
You can't buy a human, Eric.
Why not?

20:39.614 --> 20:41.114
Because...

20:42.783 --> 20:45.660
It's against the law, isn't it?
Absolutely.

20:45.828 --> 20:48.955
Mr. Morehouse,
doesn't my daddy make the laws?

20:50.458 --> 20:51.458
[CLEARS THROAT]

20:51.626 --> 20:54.252
I think he's got a point there.

20:54.462 --> 20:55.921
ERlC:
Mr. Morehouse.

20:57.381 --> 20:59.966
Now.
Now?

21:00.134 --> 21:01.927
It's your department.

21:04.013 --> 21:06.932
Good choice.
You'll have a wonderful time.

21:07.099 --> 21:08.850
[SCREAMS]

21:09.727 --> 21:12.562
Tim O'Brien, Toys.
Jack Brown, Windows.

21:12.772 --> 21:15.857
Hey. Remember me?
I'm fired, right?

21:16.025 --> 21:19.361
No, no.
Do you see that kid over there?

21:19.820 --> 21:22.489
Jesus Christ. Yeah.

21:22.657 --> 21:25.033
Well, he is the son of our--

21:25.201 --> 21:26.284
Boss.
Right.

21:26.452 --> 21:29.871
He's bright. Phi Beta.
I see the resemblance.

21:30.039 --> 21:32.540
Yeah. He'd like to take you
home with him.

21:32.708 --> 21:35.377
He would-- What?
It's just a joke.

21:35.753 --> 21:37.170
What, is he sick?
No.

21:37.338 --> 21:38.672
Nuts, right?
No.

21:38.839 --> 21:40.548
What are we talking about?

21:40.716 --> 21:42.884
He's just used to
getting his own way.

21:43.386 --> 21:46.388
You guys are serious!
No jive.

21:46.597 --> 21:49.724
You want me to go with him?
If you wouldn't mind.

21:49.934 --> 21:53.436
Oh, l mind.
I don't want him throwing a tantrum.

21:53.646 --> 21:55.563
He can do a lot of damage.

21:55.731 --> 21:58.066
I don't care.
I'm not going anywhere.

21:58.275 --> 21:59.484
No, sir. Not me.

21:59.694 --> 22:03.989
No now. No tomorrow.
No next week. I'm not-- No!

22:04.198 --> 22:06.741
No! As you say, you know? No.

22:06.909 --> 22:10.370
I think we have to butter your bread.
I don't care if you--

22:10.538 --> 22:14.040
No! Hell no. You can't--
I can't be bought.

22:14.250 --> 22:17.585
This got settled in the Civil War.
You can't have slaves. No!

22:17.753 --> 22:21.715
We're not trying to buy you.
We just want to rent you
for a little while.

22:21.924 --> 22:24.843
What is your hourly rate?
I don't have...

22:25.011 --> 22:26.594
No. No.

22:26.762 --> 22:29.139
By the hour.
No.

22:29.306 --> 22:31.725
No. Now, l don't have to stay long?

22:31.892 --> 22:33.685
Oh, no.
No.

22:33.853 --> 22:36.521
You'll give a decent burial
to Wonder Wheel?

22:36.731 --> 22:38.398
Oh, yes.
That's my friend.

22:38.607 --> 22:40.483
This is light.
Well...

22:40.651 --> 22:43.570
Thank you. Ah! Ha-ha.
Yes.

22:43.779 --> 22:46.281
It's a little light here.
Thank you.

22:46.490 --> 22:49.034
A little light.
Yes, okay, fine.

22:49.201 --> 22:50.869
JACK:
Very pleased to meet you.

22:51.078 --> 22:53.621
This is Eric.
Eric, he would be delighted.

22:53.831 --> 22:56.374
His name is Jack Brown.
Jack, Master Bates.

22:56.542 --> 22:57.625
[LAUGHS]

22:57.793 --> 22:58.793
Mas--

22:58.961 --> 23:00.045
Ah.

23:01.922 --> 23:03.298
Wrap him up.

23:03.466 --> 23:07.135
Wrap who up? Hey, Jack.
Wrap what? l don't get wrapped.

23:07.344 --> 23:11.056
I can't be wrapped unless you have
ribbon or something soft.

23:11.223 --> 23:13.058
This is still light.

23:13.559 --> 23:15.560
[♪♪♪]

23:18.439 --> 23:20.774
Elbows off the table.

23:22.485 --> 23:24.819
Sit up, Eric.

23:27.740 --> 23:31.785
Now, Eric, our stomachs digest
our food a lot better

23:31.994 --> 23:35.830
if we eat some vegetables,
some starch and some meat.

23:35.998 --> 23:40.001
In that order.
Not all the vegetables
at one time.

23:40.169 --> 23:43.171
I hate liver.
I understand nothing but German.

23:43.380 --> 23:45.006
I hate German.

23:46.550 --> 23:48.218
Well, Eric,

23:48.552 --> 23:51.262
it certainly is a pleasure
to have you.

23:51.472 --> 23:53.348
Now, what do you want
to do first?

23:54.058 --> 23:57.519
Six Flags? Delta Queen?
New Orleans?

23:57.686 --> 24:00.188
You know, I have a new helicopter.

24:06.112 --> 24:07.362
How's school?

24:10.658 --> 24:12.200
How's your math?

24:17.039 --> 24:18.206
How are the boys?

24:21.377 --> 24:22.377
Eric.

24:23.379 --> 24:26.047
Does Fancy have to come
to Six Flags with us?

24:26.215 --> 24:29.175
Certainly not. Do you want
Barkley to take you?

24:29.385 --> 24:31.761
I want you to take me.

24:34.348 --> 24:39.894
Eric, I've got a surprise for you.
Your present's arrived. Ha-ha-ha.

24:40.062 --> 24:42.689
FRÄULEIN:
Not until you finish your liver!

24:42.898 --> 24:44.816
Now just a minute here!

24:46.235 --> 24:49.195
Boys will be boys, God bless him.

24:50.239 --> 24:52.240
[TOYS BEEplNG]

24:57.413 --> 25:00.415
Eric, come and finish your dinner.
Get me a hammer.

25:00.624 --> 25:03.251
Not until you finish.
Get me a hammer.

25:03.419 --> 25:06.254
If you don't come
and finish your dinner,

25:06.422 --> 25:08.715
you will not open that
until tomorrow.

25:08.924 --> 25:10.341
JACK:
Are you crazy?

25:10.509 --> 25:14.095
[SCREAMlNG]

25:14.346 --> 25:16.014
What's going on in here?

25:16.223 --> 25:20.101
She won't help me open my present.
She won't give me a hammer.

25:21.145 --> 25:24.230
What the hell is that?
JACK: Help!

25:24.398 --> 25:25.940
Oof.

25:26.275 --> 25:28.276
You said I could have anything.

25:29.153 --> 25:31.779
JACK:
Help, please. I need air.

25:31.947 --> 25:33.948
Schatzie, get a hammer.

25:35.492 --> 25:38.995
JACK: Can I have some air?
Who are you?

25:39.205 --> 25:43.875
JACK:
I'm the new part-time cleaning lady,
sir, at the store.

25:45.544 --> 25:47.295
What are you doing in there?

25:47.504 --> 25:50.131
JACK:
Your son came along
and asked them

25:50.299 --> 25:52.800
to wrap me up,
which they did, in a box.

25:52.968 --> 25:54.636
This box.

25:56.889 --> 26:01.517
I hope you have
a good explanation for this.

26:01.727 --> 26:05.480
You said anything in the store.
Well, he was in the store.

26:07.650 --> 26:10.526
I get to open it. lt's my present.

26:10.736 --> 26:12.320
JACK:
What?

26:15.115 --> 26:16.991
Hurry!

26:18.160 --> 26:19.994
Please hurry.

26:28.128 --> 26:30.129
[♪♪♪]

26:30.547 --> 26:32.382
[GROANING]

26:41.558 --> 26:43.518
Didn't l tell you to shave?

26:43.727 --> 26:46.604
Sorry.
Sir.

26:48.315 --> 26:49.857
Sorry, sir.

26:50.734 --> 26:53.903
I mean, come here.
No way.

26:55.864 --> 26:59.659
[FlRECRACKERS EXPLODlNG
AND JACK SCREAMS]

26:59.827 --> 27:02.829
U.S.:
Now, wait a minute.
Let's not be too hasty.

27:03.038 --> 27:05.790
I'll pay you on an hourly basis.
Sir?

27:06.542 --> 27:09.752
All right, l'll pay you
on an hourly basis, sir.

27:09.962 --> 27:11.045
No way.

27:11.213 --> 27:14.799
Well, what sort of a position
are you looking for?

27:15.009 --> 27:19.304
Slave sound too crass?
I'm serious.

27:19.513 --> 27:21.889
I am too. I'm a journalist.

27:22.057 --> 27:24.559
I've been trying to get a job
on your newspaper.

27:24.727 --> 27:28.062
The only black people you hire
do windows, mop floors.

27:28.230 --> 27:32.608
I don't like it. I tried it.
Believe me, l have dignity.

27:32.818 --> 27:36.070
Take those firecrackers and--
Never mind.

27:39.450 --> 27:43.661
That's not the way out.
Go get him, Daddy.

27:44.496 --> 27:47.707
Wait a minute. What's your name?
Brown. Jack Brown.

27:47.916 --> 27:51.085
I only have the boy
for one week a year.

27:51.253 --> 27:54.005
Get better lawyers.
That's too long.

27:54.214 --> 27:57.884
I love him.
Frankly, Scarlett, I don't give a damn.

27:58.093 --> 28:02.263
He wants you to stay.
He wants to see if you can make me.

28:02.431 --> 28:05.308
He's a manipulative bastard.
It's a power play.

28:06.352 --> 28:10.104
You know, if you were
a little less hysterical,

28:10.272 --> 28:14.442
you'd suggest l pay you
what I pay my reporters for a week.

28:14.860 --> 28:17.820
Four hundred dollars.
For babysitting?

28:18.447 --> 28:19.989
Step in my office.

28:21.241 --> 28:23.242
[♪♪♪]

28:24.411 --> 28:27.663
U.S.:
Isn't that a magnificent
arrangement of dominoes?

28:27.831 --> 28:29.832
JACK:
Yes, sir. It's really something.

28:30.042 --> 28:33.753
It took me over a month to set that up.
A month? Wow.

28:33.921 --> 28:36.631
Yeah. lt's rewarding.
Have a seat.

28:45.724 --> 28:50.645
You know, Mr. Brown, I'm a man
that gets what he wants by patience.

28:50.854 --> 28:54.524
Some people exercise
their tibias, their fibulas...

28:54.817 --> 28:57.318
I exercise my patience.

29:02.157 --> 29:04.158
[LIGHTER CLICKING]

29:08.997 --> 29:10.623
Patience.

29:12.501 --> 29:14.335
There's no hole.

29:14.545 --> 29:18.256
Just bite the end off.
And spit it in your hand.

29:26.557 --> 29:31.477
Eric's not a bad boy.
High-spirited. l like that.

29:31.687 --> 29:33.271
I like him.

29:33.564 --> 29:36.065
You'll like him.
I'm crazy about him already.

29:36.275 --> 29:40.027
I want him to understand that money
means never saying you're sorry.

29:40.195 --> 29:44.198
That's about the only thing
the kid does understand.

29:45.659 --> 29:48.453
That's not an ashtray, you asshole.

29:48.954 --> 29:50.913
That's an ashtray.

29:53.542 --> 29:54.876
Okay.

29:55.919 --> 29:57.503
Ashtray.

29:57.713 --> 30:01.048
What you're offering me
isn't a job. lt's an insult.

30:01.258 --> 30:04.510
And l'm insulted and I'm splitting.

30:06.388 --> 30:09.557
All right, what do you need?

30:09.892 --> 30:11.642
I need?

30:11.894 --> 30:13.978
Ten thousand dollars.
Ten--

30:14.188 --> 30:16.606
You're not a newspaperman.
You're a crook.

30:16.815 --> 30:19.775
You asked me what I needed,
not what I'd settle for.

30:20.027 --> 30:21.736
That's what l meant, of course.

30:21.904 --> 30:24.906
Let's start at a thousand.
We'll work our way up.

30:25.073 --> 30:26.741
A thousand is highway robbery.

30:26.909 --> 30:29.744
I'd settle for 400
and a job on The Bugle.

30:29.995 --> 30:32.955
There isn't any job on the paper.

30:33.916 --> 30:36.292
A thousand five hundred.
That's a deal.

30:37.211 --> 30:39.754
Two thousand.
Now, wait a minute.

30:40.088 --> 30:41.172
We had a deal.

30:41.632 --> 30:45.301
Two-five.
All right, but for that kind of money,

30:45.511 --> 30:48.095
if Eric blows his nose,
you wipe it.

30:49.264 --> 30:51.349
Three thousand.
Two-five.

30:51.558 --> 30:54.268
Two-seven.
Two-five is my top.

30:54.478 --> 30:56.187
Three thousand dollars.

30:56.355 --> 31:00.441
I wonder if Eric knows what kind
of a bastard he's getting.

31:01.401 --> 31:04.070
I may be a bastard, Mr. Bates,
but I--

31:04.905 --> 31:07.907
[MOANlNG]

31:15.749 --> 31:17.375
[GROWLING]

31:17.543 --> 31:21.128
Aah! Ah. Oh.

31:25.384 --> 31:27.802
I'm going to kill you!
Two-five is fine.

31:27.970 --> 31:29.470
Two-five is excellent.

31:29.638 --> 31:31.681
Are you at the store?

31:32.474 --> 31:36.060
Well, where are you?
At U.S. Bates' house?

31:36.812 --> 31:39.814
The U.S. Bates' house?
Clifford, hold it down.

31:39.982 --> 31:44.360
I'm working for U.S. Bates.
''I'm working for U.S. Bates.''

31:44.570 --> 31:45.903
Not on the paper, no.

31:46.154 --> 31:47.405
A toy?

31:47.614 --> 31:52.159
I'm U.S. Bates' toy. l'm not stoned.
Let's play. Get off the phone!

31:52.369 --> 31:56.497
No, he's not playing with me.
I'm his son's toy. Eric.

31:56.665 --> 31:59.000
He's got a son and he hired me--

31:59.167 --> 32:03.212
He's one of the nicest kids
I've ever met. He's really--

32:03.422 --> 32:05.506
Play with me!
He's wonderful.

32:05.716 --> 32:08.759
Ask me how much l'm making.
Get off the phone.

32:08.969 --> 32:11.137
Get off the phone!
Ask me. Just ask.

32:11.346 --> 32:15.600
Twenty-five hundred dollars a week!
Get off the phone!

32:15.767 --> 32:18.185
Yes!
Say goodbye! Get off the phone!

32:18.353 --> 32:20.479
Come on!
No, but he's a wonderful--

32:20.689 --> 32:24.275
He's just wonderful.
You're paid to play, not to talk.

32:24.484 --> 32:26.902
Just a minute. How old are you?
Nine.

32:27.195 --> 32:30.531
You want to live to be 1 0? Do you?

32:35.203 --> 32:36.871
Oh, hi.

32:37.080 --> 32:40.291
Fancy.
Wait until l'm done, U.S.

32:41.418 --> 32:44.420
I've got to talk to you.
But I'm busy.

32:44.630 --> 32:47.715
What l have to tell you is important!

32:48.216 --> 32:50.509
What am I supposed to do?

32:50.677 --> 32:53.512
How do you turn off
this goddamn machine?

32:54.056 --> 32:57.892
Oh. Oh, sugar. I like it like that.

32:58.393 --> 32:59.727
Oh. Heh.

32:59.895 --> 33:03.022
[GlGGLING]

33:06.568 --> 33:11.197
Whee. That was fun.
Please. I have a headache.

33:11.406 --> 33:13.074
I've got something to tell you.

33:13.283 --> 33:17.244
Is it about the party? Everything's
arranged. lt'll be beautiful.

33:17.746 --> 33:19.455
It's about Eric.

33:20.499 --> 33:23.876
Oh, God.
Has it been a year already?

33:24.086 --> 33:26.087
I forgot it was his week.

33:26.296 --> 33:30.591
What do I have to do with him?
Take him to Six Flags?

33:31.718 --> 33:33.010
He, uh...

33:34.262 --> 33:35.805
He bought a black man.

33:37.349 --> 33:41.852
I wasn't aware that we sold them.
I wanted you to know,

33:42.062 --> 33:45.314
so you wouldn't be frightened
if you saw him.

33:45.524 --> 33:48.192
There's a real, live
black man in this house?

33:48.360 --> 33:50.194
It's only for a week.

33:50.612 --> 33:54.990
But why?
Heh. To play with, he says.

33:55.200 --> 33:57.827
To aggravate you and me, l say.

33:58.245 --> 34:01.831
Heaven forbid.
You just tell him no, you ass.

34:02.999 --> 34:06.168
That's U.S., not ''you ass.''

34:07.045 --> 34:11.590
Well, l'm just gonna
take a shower, U.S.

34:13.009 --> 34:15.010
[♪♪♪]

34:26.440 --> 34:27.481
[CHUCKLES]

34:27.649 --> 34:28.690
ERlC:
Look out!

34:28.900 --> 34:31.025
That's my bedroom over here.
What? Jeez.

34:35.489 --> 34:36.657
[SPEAKS GERMAN]

34:36.824 --> 34:39.744
I know nothing!
Oh, Eric!

34:40.871 --> 34:43.581
[GASPS THEN SCREAMS]

34:43.790 --> 34:46.292
This is fun, Jack.
JACK: This is fun? Aah!

34:46.460 --> 34:47.960
Look out!

34:48.128 --> 34:50.004
[JACK SCREAMlNG]

35:07.522 --> 35:11.108
[GASPING]

35:12.611 --> 35:16.572
I didn't figure your weight
in the turn. Great ride, though.

35:16.782 --> 35:19.825
Are you all right, Master Bates?
Are you all right?

35:20.035 --> 35:21.952
[GASPING]

35:22.120 --> 35:24.747
Jesus Christ! Are you crazy?

35:24.956 --> 35:26.332
What are you doing?

35:26.541 --> 35:28.793
You're making faces.
Leave the kid alone.

35:30.545 --> 35:31.712
[GRUNTlNG]

35:31.880 --> 35:34.882
Here's a hat. Now put it on.
Let's go! Let's go!

35:35.091 --> 35:37.092
Give him a ticket. Put it on.

35:37.344 --> 35:39.345
I'm Eric Bates! Give him a ticket!

35:39.513 --> 35:41.722
Go give him a ticket! Chop, chop!

35:41.932 --> 35:44.558
What's going on?
What do you mean?

35:44.726 --> 35:48.938
Is everybody like this?
Does this go on every day?

35:49.147 --> 35:51.565
You're not allowed to talk.
He's clean!

35:51.733 --> 35:54.944
I'm clean. Thank you.
That's more than the floor is.

35:55.153 --> 35:57.321
Know what's on that floor?
No.

35:57.531 --> 35:59.406
Your dinner. Ha-ha-ha.

35:59.574 --> 36:03.577
That was my dinner?
That was my dinner, Shirley Temple.

36:03.787 --> 36:06.288
I don't care. Get in!
You don't--

36:06.498 --> 36:11.252
Got a license to drive on the steps?
I don't need one. I'm Eric Bates.

36:11.461 --> 36:13.754
You'll learn the hard way, laddie.

36:13.964 --> 36:18.509
I'm Eric Bates, U.S. Bates' son!
Is there a jail around here?

36:18.718 --> 36:20.344
A jail?
Yes!

36:20.554 --> 36:23.597
On the left.
I'm Eric Bates! Put me down!

36:24.015 --> 36:27.017
I'm U.S. Bates' son!
In the slammer, mammer.

36:27.185 --> 36:30.020
I'm Eric Bates! Put me down!

36:30.188 --> 36:32.439
[ERIC SCREAMS]

36:32.607 --> 36:37.653
Jack! Let me out of here!
Barkley, you're fired!

36:37.863 --> 36:39.989
Well played. Congratulations.

36:40.198 --> 36:43.909
Could you fix me a cheeseburger?
What's going on?

36:44.119 --> 36:46.787
I didn't hear anything.
What's going on?

36:46.955 --> 36:50.207
He was driving down the steps.
He drove through the hallway.

36:50.417 --> 36:54.044
I don't want this job.
I'm gonna lose it anyways.

36:54.254 --> 36:55.337
Dad! Dad!

36:56.214 --> 36:59.133
